commits.message:
OpTestInstallUtil: Set proxy variable in script files

The --proxy option is not populated to the kickstart/preseed files when
installing an OS; update the relevant files to recognise the variable.

Signed-off-by: Samuel Mendoza-Jonas <sam@mendozajonas.com>

op-test: Run InstallHost during DefaultSuite if scratch disk available

If the default test suite is run and a scratch disk and installation
source are available, install the provided OS once the Skiroot suite is
complete. This gives us a known environment once the Host suite starts.

This somewhat naively determines which OS is to be installed based on
the repo or ISO name. If it can't determine the name, installation is
skipped.

Fixes #203

Signed-off-by: Samuel Mendoza-Jonas <sam@mendozajonas.com>
